import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    zip_counts = data['zip_code'].value_counts()
    zip_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Zip Code')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_counts = data['city'].value_counts()
    plt.bar(city_counts.index, city_counts.values)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
from shapely.geometry import Point
import descartes

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    us_counties = gpd.read_file('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plotly/datasets/master/geojson-counties-fips.json')
    us_counties['fips'] = us_counties['id'].astype(int)
    data['fips'] = data['county'].astype(int)
    data = data.groupby(['fips']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = pd.merge(us_counties, data, on='fips', how='left')
    data = data.fillna(0)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.axis('off')
    ax.set_title('Which counties have the highest concentration of data points?', fontdict={'fontsize': '25', 'fontweight' : '3'})
    data.plot(column='counts', cmap='YlOrRd', linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor='0.8', legend=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
